{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":714,"text":"Let me ask you all a question."},{"time":4282,"text":"How much weapons-grade nuclear\nmaterial do you think it would take"},{"time":8170,"text":"to level a city the size of San Francisco?"},{"time":11554,"text":"How many of you think\nit would be an amount"},{"time":13610,"text":"about the size of this suitcase?"},{"time":17685,"text":"OK. And how about this minibus?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22327,"text":"All right."},{"time":23504,"text":"Well actually, under\nthe right circumstances,"},{"time":26222,"text":"an amount of highly enriched uranium\nabout the size of your morning latte"},{"time":31697,"text":"would be enough to kill 100,000 people"},{"time":34639,"text":"instantly."},{"time":36522,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of others\nwould become horribly ill,"},{"time":40616,"text":"and parts of the city\nwould be uninhabitable for years,"},{"time":43665,"text":"if not for decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45993,"text":"But you can forget that nuclear latte,"},{"time":48580,"text":"because today's nuclear weapons\nare hundreds of times more powerful"},{"time":54574,"text":"even than those we dropped\non Hiroshima and Nagasaki."},{"time":58891,"text":"And even a limited nuclear war\ninvolving, say, tens of nuclear weapons,"},{"time":64234,"text":"could lead to the end\nof all life on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69609,"text":"So it's really important that you know"},{"time":72907,"text":"that right now we have\nover 15,000 nuclear weapons"},{"time":78012,"text":"in the hands of nine nations."},{"time":80251,"text":"And if you live in a city\nor near a military facility,"},{"time":84904,"text":"one is likely pointed right at you."},{"time":88523,"text":"In fact, if you live in any\nof the rural areas"},{"time":91438,"text":"where nuclear weapons are stored globally,"},{"time":93944,"text":"one is likely pointed at you."},{"time":96188,"text":"About 1,800 of these weapons\nare on high alert,"},{"time":100694,"text":"which means they can be launched\nwithin 15 minutes"},{"time":104408,"text":"of a presidential command."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108228,"text":"So I know this is a bummer of an issue,"},{"time":111819,"text":"and maybe you have that --\nwhat was it? -- psychic fatigue"},{"time":114656,"text":"that we heard about a little bit earlier."},{"time":116745,"text":"So I'm going to switch gears\nfor just a second,"},{"time":119072,"text":"and I'm going to talk\nabout my imaginary friend,"},{"time":121482,"text":"who I like to think of as Jasmine,"},{"time":124292,"text":"just for a moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125662,"text":"Jasmine, at the age of 25,"},{"time":128203,"text":"is part of a generation that is more\npolitically and socially engaged"},{"time":132582,"text":"than anything we've seen in 50 years."},{"time":135011,"text":"She and her friends think of themselves"},{"time":136974,"text":"as change agents\nand leaders and activists."},{"time":140247,"text":"I think of them as Generation Possible."},{"time":144317,"text":"They regularly protest\nabout the issues they care about,"},{"time":147422,"text":"but nuclear weapons are not one of them,\nwhich makes sense,"},{"time":150854,"text":"because Jasmine was born in 1991,\nat the end of the Cold War."},{"time":155076,"text":"So she didn't grow up hearing a lot\nabout nuclear weapons."},{"time":158206,"text":"She never had to duck and cover\nunder her desk at school."},{"time":161813,"text":"For Jasmine, a fallout shelter\nis an app in the Android store."},{"time":166128,"text":"Nuclear weapons help win games."},{"time":168847,"text":"And that is really a shame,"},{"time":171305,"text":"because right now, we need\nGeneration Possible"},{"time":174603,"text":"to help us make some really important\ndecisions about nuclear weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179545,"text":"For instance, will we further reduce\nour nuclear arsenals globally,"},{"time":186005,"text":"or will we spend billions,"},{"time":188945,"text":"maybe a trillion dollars,"},{"time":191192,"text":"to modernize them so they last\nthroughout the 21st century,"},{"time":194538,"text":"so that by the time Jasmine is my age,\nshe's talking to her children"},{"time":197861,"text":"and maybe even her grandchildren"},{"time":199816,"text":"about the threat of nuclear holocaust?"},{"time":203098,"text":"And if you're paying any attention\nat all to cyberthreats,"},{"time":206028,"text":"or, for instance, if you've read\nabout the Stuxnet virus"},{"time":210019,"text":"or, for God's sake, if you've ever\nhad an email account or a Yahoo account"},{"time":213908,"text":"or a phone hacked,"},{"time":215980,"text":"you can imagine the whole new world\nof hurt that could be triggered"},{"time":220156,"text":"by modernization in a period\nof cyberwarfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223944,"text":"Now, if you're paying\nattention to the money,"},{"time":226185,"text":"a trillion dollars could go a long way"},{"time":229270,"text":"to feeding and educating\nand employing people,"},{"time":232137,"text":"all of which could reduce the threat\nof nuclear war to begin with."},{"time":236691,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237869,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":240915,"text":"This is really crucial right now,"},{"time":243392,"text":"because nuclear weapons --\nthey're vulnerable."},{"time":247274,"text":"We have solid evidence"},{"time":248885,"text":"that terrorists are trying\nto get ahold of them."},{"time":252551,"text":"Just this last spring,"},{"time":253896,"text":"when four retirees\nand two taxi drivers were arrested"},{"time":258626,"text":"in the Republic of Georgia"},{"time":260249,"text":"for trying to sell nuclear materials\nfor 200 million dollars,"},{"time":263998,"text":"they demonstrated that the black market\nfor this stuff is alive and well."},{"time":268111,"text":"And it's really important,"},{"time":269396,"text":"because there have been\ndozens of accidents"},{"time":273217,"text":"involving nuclear weapons,"},{"time":274522,"text":"and I bet most of us have never heard\nanything about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277587,"text":"Just here in the United States,"},{"time":279153,"text":"we've dropped nuclear weapons\non the Carolinas twice."},{"time":283203,"text":"In one case, one of the bombs,"},{"time":285553,"text":"which fell out of an Air Force plane,"},{"time":287749,"text":"didn't detonate"},{"time":288972,"text":"because the nuclear core\nwas stored somewhere else on the plane."},{"time":292109,"text":"In another case, the weapon\ndid arm when it hit the ground,"},{"time":296169,"text":"and five of the switches designed\nto keep it from detonating failed."},{"time":300935,"text":"Luckily, the sixth one didn't."},{"time":303521,"text":"But if that's not enough\nto get your attention,"},{"time":306973,"text":"there was the 1995 Black Brant incident."},{"time":310655,"text":"That's when Russian radar technicians saw"},{"time":312958,"text":"what they thought was a US nuclear missile"},{"time":315501,"text":"streaking towards Russian airspace."},{"time":318172,"text":"It later turned out to be\na Norwegian rocket"},{"time":320916,"text":"collecting data about the northern lights."},{"time":323522,"text":"But at that time,"},{"time":324700,"text":"Russian President Boris Yeltsin\ncame within five minutes"},{"time":328495,"text":"of launching a full-scale\nretaliatory nuclear attack"},{"time":332671,"text":"against the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336924,"text":"So, most of the world's nuclear nations"},{"time":340990,"text":"have committed to getting rid\nof these weapons of mass destruction."},{"time":345352,"text":"But consider this:"},{"time":347835,"text":"the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation\nof Nuclear Weapons,"},{"time":351183,"text":"which is the most widely adopted\narms control treaty in history"},{"time":354644,"text":"with 190 signatories,"},{"time":357398,"text":"sets no specific date by which\nthe world's nuclear-armed nations"},{"time":362716,"text":"will get rid of their nuclear weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365692,"text":"Now, when John F. Kennedy\nsent a man to the moon"},{"time":368486,"text":"and decided to bring him back,\nor decided to do both those things,"},{"time":371681,"text":"he didn't say, \"Hey, whenever\nyou guys get to it.\""},{"time":374625,"text":"He gave us a deadline."},{"time":376656,"text":"He gave us a challenge"},{"time":378502,"text":"that would have been incredible\njust a few years earlier."},{"time":382033,"text":"And with that challenge,"},{"time":383559,"text":"he inspired scientists and marketers,"},{"time":386458,"text":"astronauts and schoolteachers."},{"time":389152,"text":"He gave us a vision."},{"time":391928,"text":"But along with that vision,"},{"time":393927,"text":"he also tried to give us -- and most\npeople don't know this, either --"},{"time":397495,"text":"he tried to give us a partner"},{"time":399503,"text":"in the form of our fiercest\nCold War rival, the Soviet Union."},{"time":404948,"text":"Because part of Kennedy's vision\nfor the Apollo program"},{"time":408006,"text":"was that it be a cooperation,\nnot a competition, with the Soviets."},{"time":411817,"text":"And apparently, Nikita Khrushchev,\nthe Soviet Premier, agreed."},{"time":416007,"text":"But before that cooperation\ncould be realized,"},{"time":419347,"text":"Kennedy was assassinated,"},{"time":421042,"text":"and that part of the vision was deferred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424581,"text":"But the promise of joint innovation\nbetween these two nuclear superpowers"},{"time":429784,"text":"wasn't totally extinguished."},{"time":432305,"text":"Because in 1991, which is the year\nthat Jasmine was born"},{"time":436222,"text":"and the Soviet Union fell,"},{"time":438732,"text":"these two nations engaged in a project"},{"time":441529,"text":"that genuinely does seem incredible today"},{"time":444110,"text":"in the truest sense of that word,"},{"time":446812,"text":"which is that the US sent cash\nto the Russians when they needed it most,"},{"time":451432,"text":"to secure loose nuclear materials"},{"time":454211,"text":"and to employ out-of-work\nnuclear scientists."},{"time":457440,"text":"They worked alongside American scientists\nto convert weapons-grade uranium"},{"time":464167,"text":"into the type of fuel that can be used\nfor nuclear power instead."},{"time":468464,"text":"They called it, \"Megatons to Megawatts.\""},{"time":472202,"text":"So the result is that for over 20 years,"},{"time":475362,"text":"our two nations had a program"},{"time":478193,"text":"that meant that one in 10 lightbulbs\nin the United States"},{"time":482030,"text":"was essentially fueled\nby former Russian warheads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487530,"text":"So, together these two nations\ndid something truly audacious."},{"time":491905,"text":"But the good news is,\nthe global community has the chance"},{"time":495998,"text":"to do something just as audacious today."},{"time":500897,"text":"To get rid of nuclear weapons"},{"time":503448,"text":"and to end the supply of the materials\nrequired to produce them,"},{"time":508010,"text":"some experts tell me would take 30 years."},{"time":511219,"text":"It would take a renaissance of sorts,"},{"time":513710,"text":"the kinds of innovation that,\nfor better or worse,"},{"time":516149,"text":"underpinned both the Manhattan Project,\nwhich gave rise to nuclear weapons,"},{"time":520147,"text":"and the Megatons to Megawatts program."},{"time":523019,"text":"It would take design constraints."},{"time":525665,"text":"These are fundamental to creativity,"},{"time":528407,"text":"things like a platform\nfor international collaboration;"},{"time":532447,"text":"a date certain, which is\na forcing mechanism;"},{"time":536925,"text":"and a positive vision\nthat inspires action."},{"time":540735,"text":"It would take us to 2045."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544468,"text":"Now, 2045 happens to be\nthe 100th anniversary"},{"time":548973,"text":"of the birth of nuclear weapons\nin the New Mexico desert."},{"time":553247,"text":"But it's also an important date\nfor another reason."},{"time":556458,"text":"It's predicted to be the advent\nof the singularity,"},{"time":561011,"text":"a new moment in human development,"},{"time":563431,"text":"where the lines between artificial\nintelligence and human intelligence blur,"},{"time":569106,"text":"where computing and consciousness\nbecome almost indistinguishable"},{"time":573559,"text":"and advanced technologies help us solve\nthe 21st century's greatest problems:"},{"time":579215,"text":"hunger, energy, poverty,"},{"time":582133,"text":"ushering in an era of abundance."},{"time":586318,"text":"And we all get to go to space"},{"time":587924,"text":"on our way to becoming\na multi-planetary species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592039,"text":"Now, the people who really believe\nthis vision are the first to say"},{"time":595915,"text":"they don't yet know precisely\nhow we're going to get there."},{"time":599618,"text":"But the values behind their vision"},{"time":602434,"text":"and the willingness to ask \"How might we?\""},{"time":605789,"text":"have inspired a generation of innovators."},{"time":608884,"text":"They're working backward\nfrom the outcomes they want,"},{"time":612380,"text":"using the creative problem-solving methods\nof collaborative design."},{"time":616608,"text":"They're busting through obstacles."},{"time":618872,"text":"They're redefining\nwhat we all consider possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623513,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":625706,"text":"that vision of abundance isn't compatible"},{"time":629940,"text":"with a world that still relies\non a 20th-century nuclear doctrine"},{"time":636169,"text":"called \"mutually assured destruction.\""},{"time":640945,"text":"It has to be about building\nthe foundations for the 22nd century."},{"time":646446,"text":"It has to be about strategies\nfor mutually assured prosperity"},{"time":652276,"text":"or, at the very least,\nmutually assured survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657175,"text":"Now, every day, I get to meet\npeople who are real pioneers"},{"time":662422,"text":"in the field of nuclear threats."},{"time":664363,"text":"As you can see, many of them\nare young women,"},{"time":667888,"text":"and they're doing fiercely\ninteresting stuff,"},{"time":670488,"text":"like Mareena Robinson Snowden here,\nwho is developing new ways,"},{"time":675015,"text":"better ways, to detect nuclear warheads,"},{"time":677701,"text":"which will help us\novercome a critical hurdle"},{"time":679948,"text":"to international disarmament."},{"time":681906,"text":"Or Melissa Hanham, who is using\nsatellite imaging"},{"time":684799,"text":"to make sense of what's going on\naround far-flung nuclear sites."},{"time":689358,"text":"Or we have Beatrice Fihn in Europe,"},{"time":692079,"text":"who has been campaigning\nto make nuclear weapons illegal"},{"time":696376,"text":"in international courts of law,"},{"time":698084,"text":"and just won a big victory\nat the UN last week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704202,"text":"And yet,"},{"time":705942,"text":"and yet,"},{"time":707797,"text":"with all of our talk in this culture\nabout moon shots,"},{"time":711239,"text":"too few members of Generation Possible\nand those of us who mentor them"},{"time":715991,"text":"are taking on nuclear weapons."},{"time":718524,"text":"It's as if there's a taboo."},{"time":721898,"text":"But I remember something Kennedy said\nthat has really stuck with me,"},{"time":726597,"text":"and that is something to the effect"},{"time":728379,"text":"that humans can be as big as the solutions"},{"time":730545,"text":"to all the problems we've created."},{"time":732427,"text":"No problem of human destiny, he said,"},{"time":735685,"text":"is beyond human beings."},{"time":739296,"text":"I believe that."},{"time":741376,"text":"And I bet a lot of you here\nbelieve that, too."},{"time":744535,"text":"And I know Generation\nPossible believes it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748646,"text":"So it's time to commit to a date."},{"time":753183,"text":"Let's end the nuclear weapons chapter"},{"time":756735,"text":"on the 100th anniversary of its inception."},{"time":761119,"text":"After all, by 2045, we will have held\nbillions of people hostage"},{"time":765869,"text":"to the threat of nuclear annihilation."},{"time":768167,"text":"Surely, 100 years will have been enough."},{"time":771512,"text":"Surely, a century of economic development"},{"time":775215,"text":"and the development of military strategy"},{"time":778634,"text":"will have given us better ways\nto manage global conflict."},{"time":782802,"text":"Surely, if ever there was a global\nmoon shot worth supporting,"},{"time":787759,"text":"this is it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789846,"text":"Now, in the face of real threats --"},{"time":792484,"text":"for instance, North Korea's recent\nnuclear weapons tests,"},{"time":795504,"text":"which fly in the face of sanctions --"},{"time":797808,"text":"reasonable people disagree"},{"time":800132,"text":"about whether we should maintain\nsome number of nuclear weapons"},{"time":804055,"text":"to deter aggression."},{"time":806550,"text":"But the question is:\nWhat's the magic number?"},{"time":810205,"text":"Is it a thousand?"},{"time":812140,"text":"Is it a hundred? Ten?"},{"time":815246,"text":"And then we have to ask:"},{"time":817395,"text":"Who should be responsible for them?"},{"time":820038,"text":"I think we can agree, however,"},{"time":821920,"text":"that having 15,000 of them\nrepresents a greater global threat"},{"time":825993,"text":"to Jasmine's generation than a promise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829184,"text":"So it's time we make a promise"},{"time":832366,"text":"of a world in which we've broken\nthe stranglehold"},{"time":835103,"text":"that nuclear weapons have\non our imaginations;"},{"time":838625,"text":"in which we invest\nin the creative solutions"},{"time":841261,"text":"that come from working backward\nfrom the future we desperately want,"},{"time":845015,"text":"rather than plodding forward\nfrom a present"},{"time":847573,"text":"that brings all of the mental models\nand biases of the past with it."},{"time":852392,"text":"It's time we pledge our resources\nas leaders across the spectrum"},{"time":857718,"text":"to work on this old problem in new ways,"},{"time":861146,"text":"to ask, \"How might we?\""},{"time":864001,"text":"How might we make good on a promise"},{"time":866328,"text":"of greater security\nfor Jasmine's generation"},{"time":869929,"text":"in a world beyond nuclear weapons?"},{"time":874116,"text":"I truly hope you will join us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877782,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878969,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":882295,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883992,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}